description: An abstract watercolor painting on paper I made in 2008, during an Art Trialogue with the artists Albert de Wilde en Herman van de Poll. I call it 'Color Pride'. We all three painted abstracted and wanted to talk with each others just in images. This reaction of my became a spontaneous brush painting in watercolour. This free art image is suitable for making large art posters, prints and wallpapers - Free image in paint, in public domain CCO - free download, by Fons Heijnsbroek, Dutch painter artist.
